  "course_description": "Nutrition and Chronic Disease provides an overview of the role of nutrition in chronic disease prevention, development and treatment.",
  "course_notes": "This course will explore current evidence relating diet, nutrition, and the food environment to promoting health and preventing disease. The focus will be on digestive health, obesity type 2 diabetes, cardiovascular disease, bone health, and cancer. Students will learn about diet and related factors that increase or decrease risk of these conditions, evaluate evidence, and compare intervention strategies. (Prerequisite: HLTH 220)",
